    "_comment3": "This file contains minimal test fixtures for validating the engine.",
    "_comment4": "It covers: Race (Human), Class (Fighter with levelProgression),",
    "_comment5": "Item (Longsword), Condition (Raging), Orc Enemy (for situational test).",
    "_comment6": "ALL entities have ruleSource: 'test_mock' — enable this source in",
    "_comment7": "CampaignSettings.enabledRuleSources to use these fixtures.",
    "_comment8": "=================================================================",
    "_comment9": "TARGETID CONVENTION FOR MODIFIERS:",
    "_comment10": "The `targetId` in a Modifier must match the KEY used in the Character's",
    "_comment11": "pipeline records. Per GameEngine.svelte.ts createEmptyCharacter():",
    "_comment12": "  - Main attributes:  'stat_strength', 'stat_dexterity', 'stat_constitution', etc.",
    "_comment13": "    (stored in Character.attributes — key prefix is the pipeline ID itself)",
    "_comment14": "  - Combat stats:     'combatStats.ac_normal', 'combatStats.base_attack_bonus', etc.",
    "_comment15": "    (stored in Character.combatStats — key includes the namespace prefix)",
    "_comment16": "  - Saving throws:    'saves.fortitude', 'saves.reflex', 'saves.will'",
    "_comment17": "    (stored in Character.saves — key includes the namespace prefix)",
    "_comment18": "  - Skills:           'skill_climb', 'skill_jump', etc.",
    "_comment19": "    (stored in Character.skills — key is the skill ID without namespace)",
    "_comment20": "NOTE: ARCHITECTURE.md section 4.3 shows paths like '@attributes.stat_strength'",
    "_comment21": "(with the 'attributes.' prefix) for Math Parser @-paths. However, the",
    "_comment22": "modifier targetId uses the Character record KEY directly (e.g., 'stat_strength').",
    "_comment23": "The GameEngine's DAG phases use the key directly when iterating records.",
    "_comment24": "================================================================="
  },
